# A same-operator arithmetic chain (+, -, *, ==, ...) carrying same-line
# trailing comments aligns those comments in a column, like a | / & chain.
# Unlike | / &, the arms are rendered through binaryExprPrec's operand
# path so the precedence-aware spacing is preserved: in `mixed`, the
# higher-precedence `f*g` stays compact while the chain's `+` is spaced,
# even though the comments column-align. The head comment stays inline;
# the field's own trailing comment (`third`/`gamma`) folds into the last
# row so it aligns too.
#
# Alignment is gated on same-line (Line) comments at the top level. With
# RelPos stripped (out/norelpos) the Line signal is gone, so the chain
# falls back to binaryExprPrec, which places the comments on their own
# lines - matching how any other own-line comment between operator and
# operand renders.
-- in.cue --
pure: bb + // first
	c + // second
	dddd // third
mixed: ee + // alpha
	f * g + // beta
	hhhh // gamma
-- out/relpos --
pure: bb + // first
	c +  // second
	dddd // third
mixed: ee + // alpha
	f*g + // beta
	hhhh  // gamma
-- out/norelpos --
pure: bb +
	// first
	c +
	// second
	dddd // third
mixed: ee +
	// alpha
	f*g +
	// beta
	hhhh // gamma
